{
  "target": "pearson3",
  "kind": "pearson3",
  "source_test": "HEC.FDA.StatisticsTests/Distributions/PearsonIIITests.cs (PearsonIII_InverseCDF)",
  "note": "PearsonIII.cs is a public plain helper class, not an IDistribution. `construct.params` is [mean, sd, skew, sampleSize] matching the PearsonIII(mean, sd, skew, n) ctor. All InlineData cases use skew=1.323 (positive skew -> ShiftedGamma branch); the no-skew (Normal) and negative-skew (reflection) branches have no dedicated upstream fixture case but are transcribed verbatim in pearson3.hpp per the C# source. tol/mode mirror the upstream test's own assertion: `percent = Math.Abs((output - result) / output); Assert.True(percent < .01)` -> mode rel, tol 0.01.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "name": "usgs_r_smwr_p0998",
